The Telegraph - Calcutta
 Friday, October 04, 2002 				 Two into One
																								This English sit-com is set in the Westminster Hotel, London. Richard Willey is an MP in the Conservative government. George is his special assistant. Richard and his neglected wife, Pamela, are sta ying at the hotel along with a suspicious Labour MP, Lily Chatterton. Lily is preoccupied with pornography and corruption. Richard plans an assignation with one of the Prime Ministers secretaries  the beautiful Jennifer Bristow and coerces George into helping him. George, unwittingly, finds himself at the receiving end of Pamelas advances. The antics of a Chinese waitress, a Spanish chambermaid, an irate Manager, an unsuspecting Mr Bristow and a suspicious Labour MP, inadvertently, ensure that the assignation fails amidst chaos, embarrassment and laughter. Written by Ray Cooney and directed by Dean Turner, this Limelight production features well-known theatre personalities including Pradip Mitra, Punam Singh, Girish Mansata, Debjani Roy Chatterjee and Deepika Jaidka. The proceeds of the sale will be donated to the Indian Institute of Cerebral Palsy.																								When: October 5 and 6 at 6.30 pm																								Where: G.D. Birla Sabhagar
